cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.TR, cs.SI

The paper applies machine learning to examine travel behavior and model individual taste heterogeneity in travel mode choice. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes new model-agnostic interpretation tools for machine learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper focuses on transportation and mobility, which could place it in cs.TR (Transportation), and it also examines response heterogeneity, which could place it in cs.CE (Computational Economics) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
